lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;That is, of course, if &lt;a href="http://www.droptrio.com/Music/music.html"&gt;YOU&lt;/a&gt; bank roll me.&lt;div class="blogger-post-footer"&gt;&lt;img width='1' height='1' src='https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/5783643-8107676924485119665?l=www.droptrio.com%2Fblog' alt='' /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><link>http://www.droptrio.com/blog/2008/04/i-prefer-trekker.html</link><author>gerald.patrick.flanagan@gmail.com (Patrick Flanagan)</author></item><item><guid isPermaLink='false'>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-5783643.post-3991063303708330778</guid><pubDate>Wed, 20 Feb 2008 17:57:00 +0000</pubDate><atom:updated>2008-02-20T12:01:29.995-06:00</atom:updated><title>Houston Show Saturday</title><description>We'll be playing a &lt;a href="http://www.jambase.com/shows/Shows.aspx?ArtistID=&amp;VenueID=74377&amp;City=&amp;State=&amp;Zip=&amp;StartDate=&amp;EndDate=&amp;Rec=False"&gt;show&lt;/a&gt; this coming Saturday evening (2/23) at &lt;a href="http://www.tastingroomwines.com/"&gt;The Tasting Room&lt;/a&gt;, a cool little wine bar in the Uptown Galleria area. We play at 9pm. Come on by!&lt;div class="blogger-post-footer"&gt;&lt;img width='1' height='1' src='https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/5783643-3991063303708330778?l=www.droptrio.com%2Fblog' alt='' /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><link>http://www.droptrio.com/blog/2008/02/houston-show-saturday.html</link><author>noreply@blogger.com (Ian Varley)</author></item><item><guid isPermaLink='false'>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-5783643.post-6602891154433764682</guid><pubDate>Tue, 22 Jan 2008 18:09:00 +0000</pubDate><atom:updated>2008-01-22T12:11:58.851-06:00</atom:updated><title>Canceled Shows</title><description>The Elephant Room (Austin) 1-23-08&lt;br /&gt;Luna (San Antonio) 1-24-08 &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;These shows have been canceled due to a family emergency.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;-----&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Cezanne (Houston) 1-25-08&lt;br /&gt;Revolution (Bryan) 1-26-08&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Are still scheduled.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We apologize,&lt;br /&gt;Drop Trio&lt;div class="blogger-post-footer"&gt;&lt;img width='1' height='1' src='https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/5783643-6602891154433764682?l=www.droptrio.com%2Fblog' alt='' /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><link>http://www.droptrio.com/blog/2008/01/canceled-shows.html</link><author>noreply@blogger.com (nuje)</author></item><item><guid isPermaLink='false'>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-5783643.post-8625519564892173068</guid><pubDate>Tue, 15 Jan 2008 17:54:00 +0000</pubDate><atom:updated>2008-01-15T12:50:08.701-06:00</atom:updated><title>Run</title><description>This weekend Patrick and I ran the &lt;a href="http://www.chevronhoustonmarathon.com/site3.aspx"&gt;Houston Marathon&lt;/a&gt;. This was Patrick's 4th and my 1st.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If you have the means, I highly suggest doing it. The training and the satisfaction of accomplishing such a difficult goal is fairly awesome. Also, I have to say that running a marathon is a great way to see a city at a pace that lets you appreciate where you are. You pass through all sorts of neighborhoods that normally have very little in common. But on this day people of all ages, race, class, etc. line the roads in order to encourage the runners on. Many people bring sliced fruit, drinks, power bars, Kleenex, and other items needed during a long run and pass them out as you run by. Most cheer you on by name (your bib not only has a number but also your first name) and give you a high five as you pass. This was incredible to me. Complete strangers wishing everyone well. Plus, the people working the marathon (who are mostly volunteers) are the best staff ever hired to do anything. I couldn't get over how nice everyone treated each other. This really made me proud of my city. Way to go H-town.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Ian (always being the team player) stayed behind and had a &lt;a href="http://us.wii.com/"&gt;marathon of his own&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.droptrio.com/blog/uploaded_images/1shirt-724876.JPG"&gt;&lt;img style="float:left; margin:0 10px 10px 0;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://www.droptrio.com/blog/uploaded_images/1shirt-724303.JPG" border="0" alt="" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;...You can't make me take off my shirt!&lt;div class="blogger-post-footer"&gt;&lt;img width='1' height='1' src='https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/5783643-8625519564892173068?l=www.droptrio.com%2Fblog' alt='' /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><link>http://www.droptrio.com/blog/2008/01/run.html</link><author>noreply@blogger.com (nuje)</author></item><item><guid isPermaLink='false'>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-5783643.post-7619466556614368944</guid><pubDate>Sat, 05 Jan 2008 14:15:00 +0000</pubDate><atom:updated>2008-01-05T08:18:34.495-06:00</atom:updated><title>Dancing Robots</title><description>Holy rad - check out this video of dancing japanese robots, set to Drop Trio music:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;object width="425" height="355"&gt;&lt;param name="movie" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/p09QHS2a0HA&amp;rel=1"&gt;&lt;/param&gt;&lt;param name="wmode" value="transparent"&gt;&lt;/param&gt;&lt;embed src="http://www.youtube.com/v/p09QHS2a0HA&amp;rel=1" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" wmode="transparent" width="425" height="355"&gt;&lt;/embed&gt;&lt;/object&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;(Thanks to Roy in Albuquerque for the tip!)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Happy new year. Many more robots to come in 2008!&lt;div class="blogger-post-footer"&gt;&lt;img width='1' height='1' src='https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/5783643-7619466556614368944?l=www.droptrio.com%2Fblog' alt='' /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><link>http://www.droptrio.com/blog/2008/01/dancing-robots.html</link><author>noreply@blogger.com (Ian Varley)</author></item><item><guid isPermaLink='false'>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-5783643.post-6613790522285392440</guid><pubDate>Wed, 26 Dec 2007 00:53:00 +0000</pubDate><atom:updated>2007-12-25T18:55:22.896-06:00</atom:updated><title>Merry Holidays</title><description>Hope you are all having an appropriately jolly midwinter holiday season. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Quick reminder about some shows we've got coming up in January:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;div align="center"&gt;&lt;img src="http://droptrio.com/Showdates/2008_JanTour_Web_Sm.gif"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Hope to see you Texas folks there!&lt;div class="blogger-post-footer"&gt;&lt;img width='1' height='1' src='https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/5783643-6613790522285392440?l=www.droptrio.com%2Fblog' alt='' /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><link>http://www.droptrio.com/blog/2007/12/merry-holidays.html</link><author>noreply@blogger.com (Ian Varley)</author></item><item><guid isPermaLink='false'>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-5783643.post-4026766698166923577</guid><pubDate>Wed, 12 Dec 2007 05:31:00 +0000</pubDate><atom:updated>2007-12-11T23:57:51.934-06:00</atom:updated><title>Thummer</title><description>Ian was featured in an article about a new instrument called the Thummer - &lt;a href="http://www.ianvarley.com/esemplastic/2007/12/thummed.html"&gt;read more here&lt;/a&gt;. Neither confirming nor denying that you might see it in action during the &lt;a href="http://www.droptrio.com/blog/2007/11/january-shows.html"&gt;winter Texas tour&lt;/a&gt; ...&lt;div class="blogger-post-footer"&gt;&lt;img width='1' height='1' src='https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/5783643-4026766698166923577?l=www.droptrio.com%2Fblog' alt='' /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><link>http://www.droptrio.com/blog/2007/12/thummer.html</link><author>noreply@blogger.com (Ian Varley)</author></item><item><guid isPermaLink='false'>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-5783643.post-4919667453954756272</guid><pubDate>Sun, 02 Dec 2007 06:35:00 +0000</pubDate><atom:updated>2007-12-02T00:37:41.336-06:00</atom:updated><title>Happy December</title><description>Hope everyone out there in Spaceship Jazz land is having a good December. We're going "below the radar" for a few weeks, but we'll be back to touring &lt;a href="http://www.droptrio.com/blog/2007/11/january-shows.html"&gt;starting in mid January&lt;/a&gt;, with a few dates in Texas. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Peace on earth, good will to noise-making robots.&lt;div class="blogger-post-footer"&gt;&lt;img width='1' height='1' src='https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/5783643-4919667453954756272?l=www.droptrio.com%2Fblog' alt='' /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><link>http://www.droptrio.com/blog/2007/12/happy-december.html</link><author>noreply@blogger.com (Ian Varley)</author></item><item><guid isPermaLink='false'>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-5783643.post-8217181885420461626</guid><pubDate>Sat, 17 Nov 2007 07:31:00 +0000</pubDate><atom:updated>2007-11-17T01:36:27.481-06:00</atom:updated><title>January Shows</title><description>We've got 4 dates planned in TX for January:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;div align="center"&gt;&lt;img src="http://droptrio.com/Showdates/2008_JanTour_Web_Sm.gif"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Hope to see you there!&lt;div class="blogger-post-footer"&gt;&lt;img width='1' height='1' src='https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/5783643-8217181885420461626?l=www.droptrio.com%2Fblog' alt='' /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><link>http://www.droptrio.com/blog/2007/11/january-shows.html</link><author>noreply@blogger.com (Ian Varley)</author></item><item><guid isPermaLink='false'>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-5783643.post-6532691563356384827</guid><pubDate>Tue, 13 Nov 2007 04:57:00 +0000</pubDate><atom:updated>2007-11-12T23:08:03.786-06:00</atom:updated><title>Jeff's Photos &amp; New Blog</title><description>Just &lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/droptrio/sets/72157600112463442/"&gt;posted a new set of photos on Flickr&lt;/a&gt;. This one is a great bunch of B&amp;W shots by our friend &lt;a href="http://www.jeffbalke.com"&gt;Jeff Balke&lt;/a&gt; from an aftershow we played after the &lt;a href="http://www.droptrio.com/blog/2005/07/award-best-listeners.html"&gt;Houston Press Music Awards in 2005&lt;/a&gt;. Fantastic shots.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;div align="center"&gt;&lt;img src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2306/1994471701_a3e51b8acd_m.jpg"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;div align="center"&gt;&lt;img src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2372/1994450895_3ccc9c0fb1_m.jpg"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;div align="center"&gt;&lt;img src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2334/1995273656_e859d4ebf1_m.jpg"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;BTW, if you're into the music blog thing, Jeff just started one called &lt;a href="http://blogs.chron.com/brokenrecord"&gt;Broken Record&lt;/a&gt;. He's a great writer and it'll probably be a killer blog - all about the changes that are going on in the music industry these days. Give it a read, eh? Cuz &lt;a href="http://droptrio.com/Music/sets/2005-07-24_MaryJanes/DropTrio_2005-07-24_MaryJanes_01_JeffRocks_Improv.mp3"&gt;Jeff Rocks&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;div class="blogger-post-footer"&gt;&lt;img width='1' height='1' src='https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/5783643-6532691563356384827?l=www.droptrio.com%2Fblog' alt='' /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><link>http://www.droptrio.com/blog/2007/11/jeffs-photos-new-blog.html</link><author>noreply@blogger.com (Ian Varley)</author></item><item><guid isPermaLink='false'>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-5783643.post-6227964381962154218</guid><pubDate>Wed, 24 Oct 2007 17:32:00 +0000</pubDate><atom:updated>2007-10-24T12:36:47.511-05:00</atom:updated><title>Funkdaween</title><description>We're playing a show this Saturday night (10/27) at &lt;a href="http://www.danelectrosguitarbar.com"&gt;Dan Electro's Guitar Bar&lt;/a&gt; (1031 E. 24th St.). We'll be opening for &lt;a href="http://www.myspace.com/ontheone"&gt;ON THE ONE&lt;/a&gt;, a San Diego funk band featuring members of Karl Denson's Tiny Universe.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;div align="center"&gt;&lt;img src="http://www.danelectrosguitarbar.com/Portals/DEGBar/funkdaween.jpg" width=400&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Show probably starts around 9:00 pm, and from what I hear, there will be another opener - &lt;a href="http://www.myspace.com/akinaadderleyandthevintageplayboys"&gt;Akina Adderly &amp; The Vintage Playboys&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This is going to be a Halloween party, so come in costume if you want (they're giving out at $100 prize for the best costume). See you there!&lt;div class="blogger-post-footer"&gt;&lt;img width='1' height='1' src='https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/5783643-6227964381962154218?l=www.droptrio.com%2Fblog' alt='' /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><link>http://www.droptrio.com/blog/2007/10/funkdaween.html</link><author>noreply@blogger.com (Ian Varley)</author></item><item><guid isPermaLink='false'>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-5783643.post-2561456809434191455</guid><pubDate>Tue, 16 Oct 2007 19:35:00 +0000</pubDate><atom:updated>2007-10-16T14:36:19.377-05:00</atom:updated><title>Details Forthcoming</title><description>Thanks to all the folks who came out to see us on the Fall tour in the Northeast &amp; Midwest. We had a blast, and we'll post more details &amp; photos soon.&lt;div class="blogger-post-footer"&gt;&lt;img width='1' height='1' src='https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/5783643-2561456809434191455?l=www.droptrio.com%2Fblog' alt='' /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><link>http://www.droptrio.com/blog/2007/10/details-forthcoming.html</link><author>noreply@blogger.com (Ian Varley)</author></item></channel></rss>␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀